00816 /**
00817  * cvmx_dlfe_ssp_data
00818  *
00819  * DLFE_SSP_ADDR and DLFE_SSP_DATA provide direct access to the DLFE semi-static parameters.
00820  * Software must first write DLFE_SSP_ADDR to select a portion of a semi-static parameter to read
00821  * or
00822  * write. Once DLFE_SSP_ADDR has been set, a read/write to DLFE_SSP_DATA will
00823  * read/write a portion of a semi-static parameter data structure.
00824  * In general, accesses will read/write only the bottom 32-bits. However,
00825  * when reading/writing the sector antenna map, each access reads/writes
00826  * 64-bits of data. Sector antenna map information is 4 bits per
00827  * sector, with log(num antenna) in the low two bits, and (log(fft size)-9)
00828  * in the high two bits.
00829  *
00830  * These registers are intended for debugging use when the DLFE pipeline is
00831  * idle. When the DLFE pipeline is busy, read and write operations may fail
00832  * due to contention with normal processing. Software must peform a read
00833  * after any write to determine whether the write succeeded.Failed reads will
00834  * set DATA bit 63 to one.
00835  */
00836 union cvmx_dlfe_ssp_data {

00838     struct cvmx_dlfe_ssp_data_s {
00839 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
00840     uint64_t data                         : 64; /**< For most acceses, bits (31..0) read/write the semi-static parameter value. On most reads,
00841                                                          bit 63 is the RETRY bit which is set to one if the read access fails and needs to be
00842                                                          retried. When accessing the sector antenna map, accesses use all 64 bits and there is no
00843                                                          retry bit. */
00844 #else
00845     uint64_t data                         : 64;
00846 #endif
00847     } s;
